# Dependency Management

- Use `bun add <pkg>` / `bun add -d <pkg>` / `bun add -D <pkg>` to add deps. Never hand-edit `package.json` `dependencies` / `devDependencies`.
- In workspaces, add deps to a specific package with `bun add <pkg> --filter <pkgName>` or `cd <pkg-dir> && bun add <pkg>`.
- Workspace links use `"workspace:*"`; add them via `bun add <internal-pkg>@workspace:*`.
- Always use **Zod v4** (`zod@^4`). Do not install `zod@3`.
- Use `bun install` (not `npm i` / `pnpm i` / `yarn`) at the repo root.
- After installing, commit `bun.lock` (not `bun.lockb`).

## Examples

```bash
# Root dev dep
bun add -d turbo typescript

# Scoped to a workspace package
bun add zod --filter @getdesign/types

# Workspace link
bun add @getdesign/types@workspace:* --filter @getdesign/tools
```
